LEGACY PERSISTENCE ECONOMY (LPE)

A decentralized historical contribution protocol where outbound blockchain activity becomes permanent economic memory.

LPE transforms transfers into irreversible contribution events and forms a persistence-based economy built on participation, historical continuity, and social trust rather than custodial ownership alone.


---

CORE PRINCIPLE

Traditional economic systems measure:

stored value

retained ownership

balance accumulation

capital control


Legacy Persistence Economy measures:

irreversible outbound contribution

historical participation

persistent economic activity

socially recognized effort


In LPE:

ownership is temporary

contribution history persists


Economic significance is determined not by what a participant currently holds, but by what permanently left them toward the network.


---

FUNDAMENTAL SHIFT

Traditional systems define wealth as:

retained balances

asset custody

speculative appreciation


LPE redefines wealth as:

irreversible outbound economic activity

historical contribution density

persistence through time

network-recognized participation


This transforms blockchain transfers from simple balance movement into permanent contribution records.


---

HISTORICAL CONSENSUS IDENTITY

LPE naturally evolves into a historical consensus identity system.

Identity is no longer based only on:

private keys

seed phrases

custodial control


Identity instead emerges from:

historical actions

contribution lineage

social acknowledgment

persistent participation

graph relationships


If multiple recipients confirm: “This address historically contributed to me”

the network can interpret this as:

continuity proof

legacy verification

contribution authorship evidence

historical identity persistence


even if the original wallet is lost.


---

