historical

relational

graph-based

socially anchored


rather than purely custodial.


---

PROOF-OF-SEND MODEL

LPE functions as a Proof-of-Send protocol.

Outbound transfers are interpreted as irreversible contribution events.

Any blockchain with verifiable transaction history can participate:

Bitcoin

Ethereum

Solana

stablecoins

ERC20 assets

cross-chain transfers

operational spending

grants and donations


The protocol recognizes:

who sent value

to whom

how often

how persistently

across what timeframe


and converts this history into:

contribution records

persistence scores

trust topology

economic legacy

historical reputation



---

WHY RAW TRANSFER HISTORY IS INSUFFICIENT

Traditional transfer systems contain significant noise because assets can be:

resold

looped

wash-transferred

concentrated under custody

recursively extracted


This weakens historical meaning.

LPE solves this using irreversible contribution logic and non-reversible historical indexing.

The result is:

cleaner contribution signals

clearer effort attribution

stronger persistence history

reduced circular extraction



---

HYBRID ARCHITECTURE

LPE does not replace existing blockchain economies.

Base-layer assets continue functioning normally:

BTC

ETH

stablecoins

native chain assets

ERC20 tokens


These remain:

liquid

transferable

market-driven


LPE operates as a historical persistence layer above them.

The protocol observes outbound activity and records immutable contribution events independently from asset custody.


